de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.generating.impl
Class DoubleIncrementGenerator

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.generating.impl.DoubleIncrementGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Generator, GenericGenerator
public class DoubleIncrementGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements Generator

This Generator provides a sequence of DoubleConstant objects at which each value is succeeded by one that is increased respectively decreased by a specified value (1.0 by default). The starting value and the increment are customizable. It can also be toggled also return the special values Double.NaN, Double.POSITIVE_INFINITY and DOUBLE.NEGATIVE_INFINITY.

Examples sequences:

  • 0.0, 1.0, 2.0, 3.0,..., Double.MAX_VALUE
  • 0.5, -0.5, -1.5, -2.5,..., Double.MIN_VALUE
  • 5.7, 6.8, 7.9, 10,..., Double.MAX_VALUE

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-10
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

Constructor Detail

DoubleIncrementGenerator

public DoubleIncrementGenerator()
Construct the Generator with standard settings. The first Double will have a value of 0.0 and each successor will be increased by 1.0. The maximum value is Double.MAX_VALUE. Special values will not be returned.

DoubleIncrementGenerator

public DoubleIncrementGenerator(double increment)
Construct the Generator with customized settings for the increment. The starting value is 0.0 and successors always have a increased value. The maximum value is Double.MAX_VALUE. Special values will not be returned.

Parameters:
increment - The increment. By this value each Double will be greater/less than its successor.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If the increment is zero or less than zero.

DoubleIncrementGenerator

public DoubleIncrementGenerator(double startAt,
                                boolean countDown)
Construct the Generator with customized settings for the starting value and the direction. The increment is 1.0. The maximum value is Double.MAX_VALUE. Special values will not be returned.

Parameters:
startAt - The first Double returned by the generator.
countDown - If set to true, the value will be decreased with each Double provided.
